element.name: Dublin Airport Bug Hotel by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)

center.div: This Cache is only for Travel Bugs and Coins.

element.long-description:
To walk to the cache from the Airport terminal building takes about 30 minutes.
You will need to go to the main road R132,which can be crossed safely via pedestrian traffic lights opposite "The Coachmans Inn" Public House.
Then walk up past the Ulster Bank on the left the cache is located nearby.
To drive to the cache take the Old Airport road "R132" to the Cloghran Roundabout and park in the large car park beside "The Coachman’s Inn" public house at N 53 25.972 W 006 13.769
Please do not try to park on the main road beside the cache .
If you want to visit this cache using public transport, there are a number of bus route's to take from Dublin City centre, Bus's No. 33,41,41a go directly past the Airport.
The cache is a large box which is painted to help blend in to its suroundings. Care is needed when replacing the cache to prevent it being muggled
The Windsockers
element.encoded-hints: 70 meters past the money machine, align yourself in blue,knee high, watch the birdy :-)

2008-05-19T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
It's unusual for me to be at the airport with time to spare and no luggage to worry about, I'm generally flying to or from somewhere and I generally get there by bus. Today was different - dropped Mum & Dad off and then had a bit of time to spare so thought I'd finally look for this one.
Found the parking place easily enough, parked near the bank, unhooked the GPS ready for the find and... "LOW BATTERY PRESS ENTER". Feck!!! (as they say round these parts)
So, back into the car, hook up the GPS again. Switch to map mode and study the lay of the pixels. Read the clue and then plunge in.
Was very very easy to find and seems to be full of travel jeeps.
Dropped off SMOOCH which wants to go kiss the Blarney Stone (figure it'll get there faster from here than from the Burren) and picked up some assorted bugs for tomorrow's trip to the UK.
OUT: TB Viking; TB Genuine Kiwi; TB Jeep; GC Scottish Thistle IN: TB Smooch
Find # 160
[This entry was edited by Kersti.com on Monday, May 19, 2008 at 7:16:46 AM.]
